The paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning appearance information from long-term nonlocal information, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves generating superpixels, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and image retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
